article.story: DENTON, Texas -- — Jordan Ivy-Curry scored 21 points off the bench to lead UTSA over North Texas 64-62 on Saturday night. Ivy-Curry added eight rebounds and three steals for the Roadrunners (9-19, 3-12 American Athletic Conference), who snapped a seven-game losing streak. Carlton Linguard had 13 points and sank a go-ahead layup with 1:49 left to play to give UTSA the lead for good. He added six rebounds and blocked three shots. Dre Fuller Jr. made three 3-pointers and scored 12. Jason Edwards led the way for the Mean Green (14-12, 7-7) with 15 points. C.J. Noland had 12 points and Robert Allen totaled nine points and nine rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
